    "en": "Consider Metformin as the first-line agent for older adults with type 2 diabetes. It may be used safely in patients with eGFR &#60;30 mL/min/1.73 m2. However, it is contraindicated in patients with advanced renal insufficiency (eGFR &#60;15 mL/min/1.73m2 or CKD Stage 5) and should be used with caution in patients with impaired hepatic function or heart failure, because of an increased risk of lactic acidosis. Gradually increase the dose of standard-release metformin over several weeks to minimise the risk of gastrointestinal side effects. In case of gastrointestinal side effects, or a reduction in appetite, it that can be necessary a dose reduction, change to modified-release formulation, or drug elimination.",
